Gradle PluginGradle (library)Maven <p>Add the module to the buildscript classpath so the Gradle plugin can discover it:</p> <pre><code>buildscript {
    dependencies {
        classpath("io.github.beduality:terracotta-state-filesystem:&lt;version&gt;")
    }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>dependencies {
    implementation("io.github.beduality:terracotta-state-filesystem:&lt;version&gt;")
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;io.github.beduality&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;terracotta-state-filesystem&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;VERSION&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;
</code></pre> <p>Once the module is on the classpath, the <code>StateSourceFactory</code> is discovered automatically through <code>ServiceLoader</code> under the id <code>"filesystem"</code>.</p>
